Is it possible to do this job by only using a SideIntegralPostprocessor?
I know the SideIntegralPostprocessor supports the summation of values along with surfaces.
But, it seems like SideIntegralPostprocessor cannot do the calculation multipletimes like the below:
Initial A value -> Calculate B on each quadrature point and sum all B values into value C (C = summation of B[_qp] for all surfaces) based on A value -> If B value is not met criteria, then update A -> Repeat until B is fulfilled the criteria
I tried to make it as below, but I figured out this doesn't sum up all surfaces. This code just adds one element. (I guess).
Because I can't understand how to apply threadJoin().
Can you give me some advice about it?
